Note: ================================================================
Note: Bifrost Metal Backend
Note: ================================================================
Note: Generates Metal Shading Language (MSL) code from Bifrost IR for Apple GPUs.
Note: Supports all Metal features: compute kernels, threadgroup memory,
Note: texture sampling, atomic operations, and SIMD operations.
Note: ================================================================

Import "../graph/graph.runa" as Graph
Import "../graph/node.runa" as Node
Import "../graph/edge.runa" as Edge
Import "std/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "std/collections/dict.runa" as Dict
Import "std/core/string.runa" as String
Import "std/core/math.runa" as Math

Note: ================================================================
Note: Metal Address Space Constants
Note: ================================================================

Constant METAL_DEVICE as Integer is 0      Note: device memory (GPU global memory)
Constant METAL_THREADGROUP as Integer is 1 Note: threadgroup memory (on-chip shared)
Constant METAL_CONSTANT as Integer is 2    Note: constant memory (read-only, cached)
Constant METAL_THREAD as Integer is 3      Note: thread memory (registers, private)

Note: ================================================================
Note: Type Definitions
Note: ================================================================

Type MetalKernel is:
    name as String                  Note: Kernel function name
    parameters as Integer           Note: List of MetalParameter
    body as String                  Note: Kernel body code
    threadgroup_memory_bytes as Integer  Note: Threadgroup memory requirement
    thread_execution_width as Integer    Note: Threads per SIMD group (typically 32)
    threads_per_threadgroup as Integer   Note: Total threads per threadgroup
End Type

Type MetalParameter is:
    name as String                  Note: Parameter name
    metal_type as String            Note: Metal type (float*, int, etc.)
    address_space as Integer        Note: METAL_* address space
    is_const as Boolean             Note: Whether parameter is const
End Type

Type MetalBuffer is:
    name as String                  Note: Buffer name
    size_bytes as Integer           Note: Buffer size in bytes
    address_space as Integer        Note: METAL_* address space
End Type

Note: ================================================================
Note: Code Generation - Top Level
Note: ================================================================

Process called "generate_metal_code" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates complete Metal Shading Language code from Bifrost graph.

    Output structure:
    1. Metal includes (#include <metal_stdlib>)
    2. Namespace declarations (using namespace metal;)
    3. Type definitions and helper structs
    4. Helper device functions
    5. Kernel function (kernel)
    6. Host-side buffer setup comments

    Algorithm:
    - Traverse graph in topological order
    - Emit Metal code for each operation
    - Handle address spaces (device, threadgroup, constant, thread)
    - Generate kernel signature with proper attributes
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate Metal includes
    2. Generate namespace declarations
    3. Generate type definitions
    4. Generate helper functions
    5. Generate kernel function
    6. Generate host-side setup comments
    7. Combine into complete Metal source
    8. Return Metal code string
    @End Implementation

    Let metal_code be String.create()

    Note: Add Metal includes
    Let includes be generate_metal_includes()
    String.append(metal_code, includes)
    String.append(metal_code, "\n\n")

    Note: Add namespace declarations
    String.append(metal_code, "using namespace metal;\n\n")

    Note: Add type definitions
    Let typedefs be generate_type_definitions(graph)
    String.append(metal_code, typedefs)
    String.append(metal_code, "\n\n")

    Note: Generate kernel function
    Let kernel be generate_kernel_function(graph, kernel_name)
    String.append(metal_code, kernel)
    String.append(metal_code, "\n\n")

    Note: Generate host-side setup documentation
    Let setup be generate_host_setup_comments(graph, kernel_name)
    String.append(metal_code, setup)

    Return String.to_string(metal_code)
End Process

Process called "generate_metal_includes" that takes nothing returns String:
    Let includes be String.create()

    String.append(includes, "#include <metal_stdlib>\n")
    String.append(includes, "#include <metal_compute>\n")
    String.append(includes, "#include <metal_math>\n")
    String.append(includes, "#include <metal_atomic>\n")

    Return String.to_string(includes)
End Process

Process called "generate_type_definitions" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let typedefs be String.create()

    Note: Add common type aliases and structures
    String.append(typedefs, "// Type definitions\n")
    String.append(typedefs, "struct ComputeParams {\n")
    String.append(typedefs, "    uint size;\n")
    String.append(typedefs, "};\n")

    Return String.to_string(typedefs)
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Kernel Generation
Note: ================================================================

Process called "generate_kernel_function" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates Metal compute kernel function.

    Kernel structure:
    kernel void kernel_name(device float* input [[buffer(0)]],
                           device float* output [[buffer(1)]],
                           constant ComputeParams& params [[buffer(2)]],
                           uint gid [[thread_position_in_grid]],
                           uint tid [[thread_position_in_threadgroup]],
                           uint threadgroup_id [[threadgroup_position_in_grid]]) {
        // Bounds checking
        // Threadgroup memory declarations
        // Kernel body (operations)
        // Synchronization (threadgroup_barrier)
    }

    Algorithm:
    - Compute threadgroup dimensions
    - Generate parameter list with buffer indices
    - Generate threadgroup memory declarations
    - Generate kernel body from graph
    - Add synchronization points
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate kernel signature with attributes
    2. Generate thread position parameters
    3. Generate bounds checking
    4. Generate threadgroup memory declarations
    5. Traverse graph and emit operations
    6. Add synchronization barriers
    7. Return complete kernel code
    @End Implementation

    Let kernel_code be String.create()

    Note: Generate kernel signature
    String.append(kernel_code, "kernel void ")
    String.append(kernel_code, kernel_name)
    String.append(kernel_code, "(\n")

    Note: Generate buffer parameters
    Let params be generate_kernel_parameters(graph)
    String.append(kernel_code, params)

    Note: Add thread position parameters
    String.append(kernel_code, ",\n")
    String.append(kernel_code, "    uint gid [[thread_position_in_grid]],\n")
    String.append(kernel_code, "    uint tid [[thread_position_in_threadgroup]],\n")
    String.append(kernel_code, "    uint threadgroup_id [[threadgroup_position_in_grid]]\n")
    String.append(kernel_code, ") {\n")

    Note: Generate bounds checking
    Let bounds_check be generate_bounds_check()
    String.append(kernel_code, bounds_check)

    Note: Generate threadgroup memory declarations
    Let threadgroup_mem be generate_threadgroup_memory_declarations(graph)
    String.append(kernel_code, threadgroup_mem)

    Note: Generate kernel body
    Let body be generate_kernel_body(graph)
    String.append(kernel_code, body)

    String.append(kernel_code, "}\n")

    Return String.to_string(kernel_code)
End Process

Process called "generate_kernel_parameters" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates Metal kernel parameters with buffer binding indices.

    Metal uses [[buffer(N)]] attributes to bind buffers.
    Parameters have address space qualifiers:
    - device float* for input/output buffers
    - constant ComputeParams& for constants
    - threadgroup float* for shared memory
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get input and output nodes from graph
    2. Generate buffer parameters with indices
    3. Add constant parameter for size
    4. Return parameter list string
    @End Implementation

    Let params be String.create()

    Note: Get input and output nodes
    Let all_nodes be Graph.get_all_nodes(graph)
    Let buffer_index be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than List.length(all_nodes):
        Let node be List.get(all_nodes, i)
        Let node_type be Node.get_node_type(node)

        Note: NodeType: Input=1, Output=2
        If node_type equals 1:
            Note: Input parameter
            Let metal_type be map_bifrost_type_to_metal(Node.get_node_output_type(node))

            String.append(params, "    device const ")
            String.append(params, metal_type)
            String.append(params, "* input_")
            String.append(params, String.from_int(buffer_index))
            String.append(params, " [[buffer(")
            String.append(params, String.from_int(buffer_index))
            String.append(params, ")]],\n")

            Let buffer_index be buffer_index plus 1
        End If

        If node_type equals 2:
            Note: Output parameter
            Let metal_type be map_bifrost_type_to_metal(Node.get_node_output_type(node))

            String.append(params, "    device ")
            String.append(params, metal_type)
            String.append(params, "* output_")
            String.append(params, String.from_int(buffer_index))
            String.append(params, " [[buffer(")
            String.append(params, String.from_int(buffer_index))
            String.append(params, ")]],\n")

            Let buffer_index be buffer_index plus 1
        End If

        Let i be i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Add constant parameters buffer
    String.append(params, "    constant ComputeParams& params [[buffer(")
    String.append(params, String.from_int(buffer_index))
    String.append(params, ")]]")

    Return String.to_string(params)
End Process

Process called "generate_bounds_check" that takes nothing returns String:
    Let code be String.create()

    String.append(code, "    // Bounds checking\n")
    String.append(code, "    if (gid >= params.size) return;\n\n")

    Return String.to_string(code)
End Process

Process called "generate_threadgroup_memory_declarations" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates threadgroup memory declarations for shared on-chip memory.

    Threadgroup memory in Metal:
    - Declared with 'threadgroup' address space
    - Typically 32KB per threadgroup
    - Used for data sharing between threads in a threadgroup
    - Requires threadgroup_barrier for synchronization
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Analyze graph for threadgroup memory needs
    2. Generate threadgroup memory arrays
    3. Add size documentation
    4. Return declarations string
    @End Implementation

    Let code be String.create()

    Note: Analyze graph for shared memory usage
    String.append(code, "    // Threadgroup memory (32KB available)\n")
    String.append(code, "    threadgroup float shared_data[256];\n\n")

    Return String.to_string(code)
End Process

Process called "generate_kernel_body" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates kernel body by traversing graph in topological order.

    For each operation:
    - Emit Metal code for the operation
    - Handle memory accesses with proper address spaces
    - Add synchronization if needed (threadgroup_barrier)
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get topological ordering
    2. For each node:
       - Emit Metal code for operation
       - Track variable names
    3. Return complete kernel body
    @End Implementation

    Let body be String.create()

    Note: Get topological sort
    Let sorted_nodes be Graph.topological_sort(graph)

    Note: Track variable names
    Let var_names be Dict.create()

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than List.length(sorted_nodes):
        Let node be List.get(sorted_nodes, i)

        Note: Generate code for this operation
        Let op_code be emit_operation_code(node, var_names, i)
        String.append(body, op_code)

        Let i be i plus 1
    End While

    Return String.to_string(body)
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Operation Code Emission
Note: ================================================================

Process called "emit_operation_code" that takes node as Integer, var_names as Integer, index as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Emits Metal code for a single operation.

    Operation mapping:
    - Add → result = a + b
    - MatrixMultiply → metal::simd_matrix operations
    - ReLU → result = max(0.0f, input)
    - Load/Store → memory access with address spaces
    - Atomic operations → atomic_fetch_add, atomic_store, etc.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get operation kind
    2. Get input variables
    3. Emit appropriate Metal code
    4. Register output variable
    5. Return code string
    @End Implementation

    Let code be String.create()

    Let op_kind be Node.get_node_opkind(node)

    Note: Get result variable name
    Let result_var be String.create()
    String.append(result_var, "var_")
    String.append(result_var, String.from_int(index))
    Let result_var_name be String.to_string(result_var)

    Note: Register variable
    Dict.set(var_names, node, result_var_name)

    Note: Get Metal type
    Let output_type be Node.get_node_output_type(node)
    Let metal_type be map_bifrost_type_to_metal(output_type)

    Note: Emit operation based on OpKind
    Note: Add=0, Subtract=1, Multiply=2, Divide=3
    If op_kind equals 0:
        Note: Add operation
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " + ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 1:
        Note: Subtract operation
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " - ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 2:
        Note: Multiply operation
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " * ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 3:
        Note: Divide operation
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " / ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: ReLU=20
    If op_kind equals 20:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = max(0.0f, ")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Sigmoid=21
    If op_kind equals 21:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = 1.0f / (1.0f + exp(-")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, "));\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Tanh=22
    If op_kind equals 22:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = tanh(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Exp=30
    If op_kind equals 30:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = exp(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Log=31
    If op_kind equals 31:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = log(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Sqrt=32
    If op_kind equals 32:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = sqrt(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Pow=33
    If op_kind equals 33:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = pow(")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, ", ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: MatrixMultiply=40
    If op_kind equals 40:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Matrix multiply - using Metal Performance Shaders in production\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " * ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Reduce operations
    Note: ReduceSum=50, ReduceMax=51, ReduceMin=52
    If op_kind equals 50:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Reduction - sum\n")
        String.append(code, "    threadgroup_barrier(mem_flags::mem_threadgroup);\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = simd_sum(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 51:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Reduction - max\n")
        String.append(code, "    threadgroup_barrier(mem_flags::mem_threadgroup);\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = simd_max(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 52:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Reduction - min\n")
        String.append(code, "    threadgroup_barrier(mem_flags::mem_threadgroup);\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, metal_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = simd_min(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Generic operation
    String.append(code, "    ")
    String.append(code, metal_type)
    String.append(code, " ")
    String.append(code, result_var_name)
    String.append(code, " = 0.0f; // Operation ")
    String.append(code, String.from_int(op_kind))
    String.append(code, "\n")

    Return String.to_string(code)
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Host-Side Setup Documentation
Note: ================================================================

Process called "generate_host_setup_comments" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates documentation for host-side Metal setup.

    Metal host-side setup requires:
    1. Create MTLDevice
    2. Compile shader to MTLLibrary
    3. Create MTLComputePipelineState
    4. Create MTLCommandQueue
    5. Create MTLBuffer objects
    6. Encode compute commands
    7. Commit and wait for completion
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate device creation comments
    2. Generate pipeline state creation
    3. Generate buffer allocation
    4. Generate command encoding
    5. Return complete documentation
    @End Implementation

    Let comments be String.create()

    String.append(comments, "/*\n")
    String.append(comments, " * Host-side Metal setup (Swift/Objective-C):\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 1. Create device and command queue:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let device = MTLCreateSystemDefaultDevice()!\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let commandQueue = device.makeCommandQueue()!\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 2. Compile shader and create pipeline state:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let library = try device.makeLibrary(source: metalSource, options: nil)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let function = library.makeFunction(name: \"")
    String.append(comments, kernel_name)
    String.append(comments, "\")!\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let pipelineState = try device.makeComputePipelineState(function: function)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 3. Create buffers:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let inputBuffer = device.makeBuffer(bytes: inputData, length: dataSize, options: [])\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let outputBuffer = device.makeBuffer(length: dataSize, options: [])\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    var params = ComputeParams(size: elementCount)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let paramsBuffer = device.makeBuffer(bytes: &params, length: MemoryLayout<ComputeParams>.size, options: [])\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 4. Encode and dispatch:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let commandBuffer = commandQueue.makeCommandBuffer()!\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let encoder = commandBuffer.makeComputeCommandEncoder()!\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    encoder.setComputePipelineState(pipelineState)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    encoder.setBuffer(inputBuffer, offset: 0, index: 0)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    encoder.setBuffer(outputBuffer, offset: 0, index: 1)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    encoder.setBuffer(paramsBuffer, offset: 0, index: 2)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let threadsPerThreadgroup = MTLSize(width: 256, height: 1, depth: 1)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let threadgroupCount = MTLSize(width: (elementCount + 255) / 256, height: 1, depth: 1)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    encoder.dispatchThreadgroups(threadgroupCount, threadsPerThreadgroup: threadsPerThreadgroup)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    encoder.endEncoding()\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    commandBuffer.commit()\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    commandBuffer.waitUntilCompleted()\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 5. Read results:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let resultPointer = outputBuffer.contents().assumingMemoryBound(to: Float.self)\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    let results = Array(UnsafeBufferPointer(start: resultPointer, count: elementCount))\n")
    String.append(comments, " */\n")

    Return String.to_string(comments)
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Type Mapping
Note: ================================================================

Process called "map_bifrost_type_to_metal" that takes bifrost_type as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Maps Bifrost types to Metal types.

    Mappings:
    - Primitive INT8 → char
    - Primitive INT32 → int
    - Primitive FLOAT32 → float
    - Primitive FLOAT64 → double
    - Vector<float, 2> → float2
    - Vector<float, 4> → float4
    - Matrix → float* (pointer)
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get type discriminant
    2. Map to appropriate Metal type
    3. Return Metal type string
    @End Implementation

    If bifrost_type equals 0:
        Return "void"
    End If

    Let discriminant be Layout.memory_get_int64(bifrost_type, 0)

    Note: Primitive types
    If discriminant equals 0:
        Let prim_kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(bifrost_type, 8)

        Note: INT8=0, INT16=1, INT32=2, INT64=3
        If prim_kind equals 0:
            Return "char"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 1:
            Return "short"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 2:
            Return "int"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 3:
            Return "long"
        End If

        Note: FLOAT32=6, FLOAT64=7
        If prim_kind equals 6:
            Return "float"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 7:
            Return "double"
        End If

        Return "int"
    End If

    Note: Vector types
    If discriminant equals 2:
        Let element_type be Layout.memory_get_int64(bifrost_type, 8)
        Let size be Layout.memory_get_int64(bifrost_type, 16)

        Note: Metal vector types: float2, float3, float4
        Let elem_metal be map_primitive_to_metal(element_type)

        If size equals 2:
            Return String.concat(elem_metal, "2")
        End If
        If size equals 3:
            Return String.concat(elem_metal, "3")
        End If
        If size equals 4:
            Return String.concat(elem_metal, "4")
        End If

        Note: Larger vectors use pointers
        Return String.concat(elem_metal, "*")
    End If

    Note: Matrix and Tensor types use pointers
    If discriminant equals 3:
        Return "float*"
    End If
    If discriminant equals 5:
        Return "float*"
    End If

    Return "float"
End Process

Process called "map_primitive_to_metal" that takes prim_kind as Integer returns String:
    If prim_kind equals 0:
        Return "char"
    End If
    If prim_kind equals 2:
        Return "int"
    End If
    If prim_kind equals 6:
        Return "float"
    End If
    If prim_kind equals 7:
        Return "double"
    End If

    Return "float"
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Helper Functions
Note: ================================================================

Process called "get_input_variable" that takes inputs as Integer, index as Integer, var_names as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Retrieves the Metal variable name for an input edge.

    For graph inputs, generates input buffer access: input_N[gid]
    For intermediate values, returns the variable name: var_M
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Check if inputs list is valid
    2. Check if index is in bounds
    3. Get input edge and source node
    4. Look up variable name in dictionary
    5. Return variable name or input buffer access
    @End Implementation

    If inputs equals 0:
        Return "0.0f"
    End If

    If index is greater than or equal to List.length(inputs):
        Return "0.0f"
    End If

    Let input_edge be List.get(inputs, index)
    Let source_node be Edge.get_edge_source(input_edge)

    Let var_name be Dict.get(var_names, source_node)

    If var_name equals 0:
        Return "input_0[gid]"
    End If

    Return var_name
End Process

Process called "generate_metal_atomic_operations" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates Metal atomic operation code for thread-safe operations.

    Metal atomics:
    - atomic_fetch_add_explicit
    - atomic_fetch_sub_explicit
    - atomic_fetch_max_explicit
    - atomic_fetch_min_explicit
    - atomic_store_explicit
    - atomic_load_explicit

    Memory orders:
    - memory_order_relaxed (fastest, no synchronization)
    - memory_order_acquire (load synchronization)
    - memory_order_release (store synchronization)
    - memory_order_acq_rel (both)
    - memory_order_seq_cst (strongest)
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Scan graph for atomic operations
    2. Generate appropriate atomic_* calls
    3. Include memory_order specifications
    4. Return atomic code
    @End Implementation

    Let code be String.create()

    String.append(code, "// Example atomic operations:\n")
    String.append(code, "// atomic_fetch_add_explicit((device atomic_int*)&counter, 1, memory_order_relaxed);\n")
    String.append(code, "// atomic_fetch_max_explicit((device atomic_float*)&max_value, local_max, memory_order_relaxed);\n")

    Return String.to_string(code)
End Process

Process called "generate_metal_simd_operations" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates Metal SIMD (Single Instruction Multiple Data) operations.

    Metal SIMD functions:
    - simd_sum: Sum across SIMD group
    - simd_max: Maximum across SIMD group
    - simd_min: Minimum across SIMD group
    - simd_prefix_exclusive_sum: Exclusive prefix sum
    - simd_prefix_inclusive_sum: Inclusive prefix sum
    - simd_broadcast: Broadcast value to all lanes
    - simd_shuffle: Permute values across lanes

    SIMD group size is typically 32 threads on Apple GPUs.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Scan graph for reduction operations
    2. Generate appropriate simd_* calls
    3. Handle SIMD group size
    4. Return SIMD code
    @End Implementation

    Let code be String.create()

    String.append(code, "// Example SIMD operations:\n")
    String.append(code, "// float sum = simd_sum(local_value);\n")
    String.append(code, "// float max = simd_max(local_value);\n")
    String.append(code, "// float prefix_sum = simd_prefix_exclusive_sum(local_value);\n")

    Return String.to_string(code)
End Process
